cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with sets of words over an alphabet and their properties.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial constructions of sets of words.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses the completeness of sets of words, which is related to the concept of entropy in information theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper involves the study of the complexity of determining whether a word is uncompletable.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper involves the construction of sets of words with specific properties, which may involve algorithmic techniques.
